# glpi-rgsupervision-sync

GLPI plugin for automatic synchronization of **RG Supervision** alerts into GLPI tickets.

![GLPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/GLPI-10.x%20%7C%2011.x-blue)
![PHP](https://img.shields.io/badge/PHP-7.4%2B-purple)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-GPL%20v2-green)
![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/Version-1.0.0-orange)

---

## How it works

The plugin queries the RG Supervision API via a dedicated cron script and:

- Creates a GLPI ticket for each new open alert, with status set to **New**
- Automatically assigns the client entity via the **GLPI TAG** matching the RG node name
- Determines the ticket category based on the entity's **active contracts**
- Adds a private follow-up task if the `raiseCount` counter increases
- Automatically resolves the ticket when the alert closes on the RG side (only if status is **New**)
- Adds a one-time private info task if the alert closes while a technician is already working the ticket
- Detects manual reopenings and manual closures performed by technicians in GLPI
- Ignores alerts whose title starts with `BC`

> **One-way synchronization** — RG Supervision → GLPI only. Closing a ticket in GLPI does **not** close the alert in RG Supervision.

