## Configuration

Access the configuration page:

```
Setup → Plugins → RG Supervision Sync → ⚙️ Configure
```

### 1. RG Supervision API

| Parameter | Description | Default |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| API Token | RG Supervision authentication token (`at_xxxx`) | — |
| API URL | Base URL of the RG API | `https://api.rg-supervision.com` |
| Root Node ID | ID of the root node in your RG Supervision tree | — |
| HTTP Timeout (s) | Maximum request delay in seconds | `30` |
| Agent types | `s` = Server, `w` = Workstation, `e` = Equipment | `s,w,e` |
| Severities | Alert levels to synchronize (Critical / Medium / Low) | Critical + Medium |

### 2. GLPI Parameters

| Parameter | Description | Default |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| Request source ID | GLPI ID of the "Supervision" request source | `10` |
| Assigned group ID | ID of the group assigned to new tickets | `9` |
| Default entity ID | Fallback entity if no TAG matches | `0` (root) |
| Resolved cleanup (days) | Purges resolved/closed entries after N days | `30` |

> To find an ID in GLPI, open the element and read `id=XX` in the browser URL.

### 3. RG Node ↔ GLPI Entity Matching

> ⚠️ **Key point** — The RG node name must match the **TAG** field of the GLPI entity.

For each client, set the entity TAG in GLPI:

```
Administration → Entities → [Client entity] → TAG = RG_NODE_NAME
```

**Example:**

| RG Supervision node | GLPI entity TAG |
|---------------------|-----------------|
| `CLIENT1` | `CLIENT1` |
| `CLIENT2` | `CLIENT2` |
| `CLIENT3` | `CLIENT3` |

Matching is performed in this order:
1. **Exact TAG** *(highest priority, case-insensitive)*
2. Exact entity name
3. Partial entity name
4. Default entity (fallback)

If no TAG matches, the ticket is created in the default entity.

### 4. Contracts → Categories

The plugin automatically assigns a GLPI category based on the entity's active contracts. Rules are fully configurable from the interface and **empty by default** on fresh install.

**A contract is considered active if:**
- Status contains `actif` (e.g. `Contrat Actif`)
- Directly assigned to the entity *(recursive parent contracts are excluded)*
- Within the `begin_date` / `end_date` range

**Example rules:**

| Contract prefix | Title keyword | Assigned category |
|---|---|---|
| `BACKUP` | `beemo` | `Contracts > Services > Managed Services > Managed Services Beemo` |
| `FIREWALL` | `watchguard` | `Contracts > Services > Managed Services > Managed Services Watchguard` |
| `SMUTILISATEURPREM` | *(empty)* | `Contracts > Services > Managed Services > Managed Services Premium` |
| `SMUTILISATEURESS` | *(empty)* | `Contracts > Services > Managed Services > Managed Services Essentials` |
| `CONTRAT ZEN` | *(empty)* | `Contracts > Services > SAPHIR` |
| `CONTRAT SAPHIR` | *(empty)* | `Contracts > Services > SAPHIR` |

Rules are evaluated in order — the first match wins. If no active contract matches, the default category is used (`Services > Out of Contract`).

### 5. Automatic synchronization (cron)

The configuration page displays the **exact crontab line** to add on the server, automatically generated based on the configured frequency.

```sh
crontab -e
# Paste the line shown in the interface, example:
*/10 * * * * /usr/local/bin/php /var/www/glpi/plugins/rgsupervision/front/runcron.php >> /tmp/rgsync.log 2>&1
```

Check the cron is active:
```sh
crontab -l
```

Test manually:
```sh
/usr/local/bin/php /var/www/glpi/plugins/rgsupervision/front/runcron.php
```

View the sync log:
```sh
tail -f /tmp/rgsync.log
```

